1), Danish folk high school teacher\n*[[Marianne Christiansen]] (born 1963), Danish bishop\n*[[Matias Christiansen]] (born 1986), Peruvian aeronautical engineer and academic\n*[[Michael Christiansen]] (1926 or 1927\u20141984),  British newspaper editor\n*[[Michele Christiansen]] (born 1970), American state appeals judge\n*[[Mogens Christiansen]] (born 1972), Danish cricketer\n\n===N===\n*[[Nina Christiansen]] (born 1964), Danish long-distance runner\n===O===\n*[[Ole Kirk Christiansen]] (1891\u20131958),  Danish carpenter and toy maker\n===P===\n*[[Peter Christiansen (footballer, born 1975)]], Danish footballer\n*[[Peter Christiansen (footballer, born 1999)]], Danish footballer\n===R===\n*[[Ragnar Christiansen]] (born 1922), Norwegian politician\n*[[Reggie Christiansen]] (born 1975), American college baseball coach\n*[[Rob Christiansen]], American musician\n*[[Rune Christiansen]] (born 1963), Norwegian poet and novelist\n*[[Rupert Christiansen]] (born 1954), English writer, journalist and critic\n\n===S===\n*[[Sabine Christiansen]] (born 1957), German journalist\n*[[Sonja Boehmer-Christiansen]] (born 1942), English academic\n*[[Sophie Christiansen]] (born 1987), British Paralympian in equestrian events\n\n===T===\n*[[Tanya Christiansen]], American mathematician\n*[[Thomas Christiansen]] (born 1973), Spanish footballer\n*[[Thor Nis Christiansen]] (1957\u20131981), American criminal\n*[[Trine Christiansen]], Danish cricketer\n\n===W===\n*[[Wilbur Norman Christiansen]] (1913\u20132007), Australian radio astronomer\n==Other==\n'''Christiansen''' may also refer to:\n\n*[[Christiansen effect]], a filtering effect\n*[[Christiansen filter]], narrow bandpass or monochromatic optical filter\n*[[Christiansen Academy]], private boarding school in Rubio, T\u00e1chira, Venezuela\n\n==See also==\n*[[Christensen (surname)|Christensen]]\n*[[Christianson]]\n*[[Kristiansen]]\n\n;References\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{surname}}\n\n[[Category:Danish-language surnames]]\n[[Category:Norwegian-langua